From rick Richard Warner Subject Re ATM or Truetype which to choose TT for True Effects for windows writes In article William Lai writes In article Yearsley writes I've just bought a PC which came with a bundle of Lotus stuff including Adobe Type Manager version As a newcomer to Windows I'm confused about which I should be using ATM or There is a program called true effects for windows that allows you to define attributes for true type fonts and have them look like new It will give your font different backgrounds or shadows or reverse It ONLY works with TT Yes and the idea was ripped off from Adobe which has had a program called TypeAlign for a few years TypeAlign does the same thing for Adobe Type fonts and Adobe has said that the next version will work with both Adobe Type and And TypeAlign does some things that TrueEffects does not including some things you apparently want If you want to use it you best not want to use it with an ATM type Oh lest you think this is a really cool program none of the effects are scalable like the brick background pattern is the same size whether your font is point of and it is not extensible you CAN NOT add pattern of your And you can't rorate the background And you can't make the pattern extend beyond one character Every character in that new font has the entire pattern in it As opposed to having the SAME pattern run contiguously through a couple of characters It is however Maybe I will buy a copy when the next version comes out if they fix some of these